Description:
The Stan Smith Grade School from adidas Originals was released in 1973 as the first full leather performance court shoe and has gone on to become an off court icon. Featuring a dimpled outsole for optimal grip and a reinforced heel for achilles support, the Stan Smith GS backed up its understated style with plenty of substance. The trademark stripes have been replaced by perforations while an all-white leather upper sports a contrasting Red heel tab with Stan himself smiling out from the tongue.
